## 4. Column Map

### Primary Data Columns (A–N)

| Column | Header (Row 3) | Data Type | Description | Written By |
|--------|---------------|-----------|-------------|------------|
| **A** | Customer | Text | Customer / company name (e.g., `"HH Global"`, `"Port City"`). Also holds **section marker text** (see §3). Yellow (`RGB(255,255,0)`) interior = priority/Must Ship indicator. | Tally pull (from source col 11 = col K) |
| **B** | WO# | Numeric text | Work order number. **4 digits = Port City**, **5 digits = Wilde Signs**. This is the primary key used to match across all external files (shipping, printing lists, proof index, emails). | Tally pull (from source col 12 = col L) |
| **C** | Description | Formula / Text | Job description. On tally-imported rows, this is a **formula**: `=IF(ISBLANK(F{row}),"", CONCATENATE("{desc}", "(" & TEXT(F{row}, "mm/dd/yy") & ")"))` — i.e., the description text with the Must Ship date appended in parens. The raw description text comes from source col 13 (col M). | Tally pull formula; also direct text on manually-entered rows |
| **D** | *(hidden)* | Text | Category/type from tally source (e.g., `"(OUTSOURCED)"`, `"(DESIGN ONLY)"`, `"(INSTALL)"`, `"(INV)"`, `"(COM)"`). **Column D is hidden** on the main sheet and on shipping copies. Used only during tally categorization. | Tally source col 4 (col D) |
| **E** | Salesperson / Source | Text | Salesperson name or source identifier. During tally import, this is populated from `srcWs.Cells(1, 2)` (cell B1 of the tally sheet — typically the salesperson's name). | Tally pull |
| **F** | Must Ship | Date | The date the job must ship. Drives the `CONCATENATE` formula in col C. Used by `TodayRowsMoveAndSort` to decide when to move rows to the CUSTOMER block. Format often `mm/dd/yy`. | Tally pull (from source col 6) |
| **G** | Proof Date | Date / `"N/A"` | Date of the latest proof file for this WO#, looked up from the proof index (`file_index.xlsx`). Set to `"N/A"` if no proof is found. Font color set to yellow if proof is missing and Must Ship date has passed. For Coming Up rows, set to `"N/A"` on import. Format: `d-mmm`. | `modProofIndex` (RunIndexingAndSearch*), `PullProofsForHHGlobal`, tally pull (N/A default for Coming Up) |
| **H** | Approval Date | Date / blank | Date the proof was approved, pulled from Outlook emails in the `approvals@wilde-signs.com` Approvals folder. Written by `FindKeywordsInEmails`. Also triggers `Worksheet_Change` → `ApprovalChange` to auto-fill cols L & M. Range `H4:H200` is monitored. | `modEmailApprovals` (ScanEmails), manual entry |
| **I** | Print/Cut Date | Date / `"N/A"` | Date of the latest print+cut file for this WO#, looked up from `PrintCut_Index.xlsx`. Set to `"N/A"` if no match. For Coming Up rows, set to `"N/A"` on import. | `modProofIndex` (RunIndexingAndSearchPrintCutPDFs) |
| **J** | Print Status | Date / Flag string | **Completion tracking from printing sub-lists.** If all assigned stations (RR, FB, Z) have marked the WO complete → stamped with today's date (format `d-mmm`). If some stations are incomplete → contains flag text like `"RR"`, `"FB"`, `"Z"`, `"RR FB"`, etc. identifying which stations still need to finish. Also read by `CreateLists_MM_FB_Zund`: if col J already contains a date, the row is skipped (already printed). | `modPrintLists` (UpdateCompletedMarks) |
| **K** | Notes | Text | Free-text notes column. `modProofIndex` appends `"m/d; Approval with missing Proof."` here when a WO has an approval date but no proof file. Multiple notes are concatenated. | `modProofIndex`, manual |
| **L** | Days (calculated) | Formula | `=IF(AND(H{row}="",F{row}=""),"",IFERROR(LET(d,NETWORKDAYS(H{row},F{row}),IF(d>365,"",d)),IFERROR(F{row}-E{row},"")))` — Network days between approval date (H) and must-ship date (F). Blank if either is missing. Suppressed if >365. | `ApprovalChange` auto-fill |
| **M** | Deadline Warning | Formula | `=IFERROR(@IF(ISBLANK(H{row}),"",IFS(L{row}<7,WORKDAY(H{row},7),L{row}>7,"")),"")`  — If fewer than 7 business days between approval and ship date, shows the 7-workday deadline from approval. Warning flag for tight timelines. | `ApprovalChange` auto-fill |
| **N** | *(implicit)* | — | Column N (col 14) is referenced as the right boundary of sort ranges. Not actively populated but included when sorting blocks. | Sort operations |

### Printing Sub-List Column Mapping

When `CreateLists_MM_FB_Zund` builds the Roll-to-Roll, Flatbed, and Zund workbooks, it copies a **subset** of columns:

| Sub-list Col | Source Col | Content |
|-------------|-----------|---------|
| A | A | Customer |
| B | B | WO# |
| C | C | Description (formula) |
| D | *(spacer, width=2)* | Cleared |
| E | E | Salesperson |
| F | F | Must Ship |
| G | J | Print Status (becomes the completion mark column on the sub-list) |

The sub-lists use **col G as the completion mark**: when a printer marks a job done on the sub-list, `UpdateCompletedMarks` reads that col G back and updates col J on the main sheet.

