## 5. Cell Styles Used

| Style Name | Applied To | Meaning |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| `"Attention"` | `A:C` of a row | Rush / Must Ship / Redo / Sample job (source tally col 7) |
| `"Normal"` | `A:C` of a row | Standard priority job |
| `"InnerWorkings"` | `A:C` of a row | HH Global / InnerWorkings row (applied during MoveAndSortRows) |
| `"Must Ship"` | `A:C` of a row | Yellow-highlighted row that has reached its Must Ship date (TodayRowsMoveAndSort) |
| `"Good"` | Col E on shipping copies | Green fill (completed column) |
| `"Input"` | Col F on shipping copies | Blue border (install ready column) |
| `"Note"` | G1:G2 on shipping copies | Yellow fill (unlisted orders header) |

Cell interior color `RGB(255,255,0)` (yellow) on column A is used as a priority flag independent of styles — `TodayRowsMoveAndSort` checks `cell.Interior.Color = RGB(255,255,0)` to allow an extra day of lead time.

