## 8. Source Tally Sheet Column Mapping

When tally data is imported, the source sheet columns map to the production list as follows:

| Source Column | # | Maps To | Production List Column |
|--------------|---|---------|----------------------|
| D | 4 | Category tag | Used for routing (`(OUTSOURCED)`, `(DESIGN ONLY)`, `(INSTALL)`, `(INV)`, `(COM)`) — not written to dest |
| E | 5 | Proof status | Used for routing (`"Yes"`, `"No"`, `"Approved"`) — not written to dest |
| F | 6 | Must Ship date | → **F** (Must Ship) |
| G | 7 | Priority flag | Used for styling (`"Must Ship"`, `"Rush"`, `"Redo"`, `"Sample"`) — not written to dest |
| K | 11 | Customer name | → **A** (Customer) |
| L | 12 | WO# | → **B** (WO#) |
| M | 13 | Description text | → **C** (as formula with Must Ship date appended) |
| B1 | — | Salesperson name | → **E** (Salesperson) |

